WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
What is an API and How It Works

2
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:06.000
An API stands for Application Programming Interface

3
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.000
It is a set of rules for software to communicate

4
00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000
APIs allow different applications to talk to each other

5
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:15.000
When you use an app, the app uses an API

6
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.000
The app sends a request through the API

7
00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.000
The server processes the request and responds

8
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
REST APIs are the most popular type today

9
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000
They use standard HTTP methods for operations

10
00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:30.000
GET method retrieves data from the server

11
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
POST method creates new data on the server

12
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.000
PUT method updates existing data on the server

13
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:39.000
DELETE method removes data from the server

14
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:42.000
Authentication is required for secure API access

15
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:45.000
An API key identifies the user making requests

16
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:48.000
Rate limiting prevents too many requests at once

17
00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:51.000
JSON is the most common data format for APIs

18
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.000
JSON is easy to read and widely supported

19
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.000
Google Maps API powers many map applications

20
00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:00.000
Twitter API allows posting and reading tweets

21
00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Stripe API handles payment processing securely

22
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:06.000
Weather APIs provide forecast data to apps

23
00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:09.000
APIs are essential for modern software development

24
00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:12.000
They enable applications to work together seamlessly
